    Class Description
    Callback
    Interface for implementing callback.

    Logic for the camera fragment, which is responsible for managing everything that pertains to scanning and adding a new QR code.
    CameraFragmentTest
    Intent tests for the camera fragment.
    CameraFragmentTest.Callback  
    CaptureAct
    Simple class that handles the opening of the camera for QR scanning by extending zxing library's CaptureActivity class.
    Comment
    This Class represents a Comment that will belong to a QRCode object.
    CommentAdapter
    This class is a custom adapter to handle Comment objects
    MainActivity
    Main app activity.
    MainActivity.mainActivityCallback  
    MapFragment
    Everything to do with google maps Asks for location permissions and zooms in on current location.
    OnItemClickListener  
    OnItemLongClickListener
    Interface to handle long clicking on the RecyclerView
    PhotoUploader
    A simple object that contains the name and image url of an uploaded photo, that is added to the "uploads" collection in the Firebase database.
    ProfileFragment
    Handles player profile screen.
    ProfileTest
    Intent tests for the Profile Fragment and its interaction with the ViewQR dialog.
    ProfileTest.Callback  
    QRAdapterClass
    Adapter class for RecyclerView that holds user's collection of QR Codes
    QRCode
    This Class is used to model a QR Code.
    QRCodeTest
    This Test class is to verify the methods of the QRCode object run as expected.
    SettingsFragment
    Handles settings screen.
    SettingsFragment.settingsCallback  
    TakePhotoActivity
    The activity responsible for taking a photo of the QR object or location, and then uploading it to Firebase.
    TakePhotoActivity.OnUploadListener
    A listener interface used to retrieve the url string after the photo has been uploaded to the db
    ViewQR
    This is the dialog fragment that appears when a user clicks to see more info about a certain QRCode.
    ViewQR.ViewQRDialogListener
    Listener for the ViewQR dialog
